*=============================================================================
* ACIA IRQ Handler Comments
*=============================================================================
comment E000 === ACIA INTERRUPT HANDLER ===
comment E000 Increment GPIB activity counter (M0x04)
comment E00B Set ACIA inhibit timer to 0x14
comment E011 Disable ACIA RX interrupts temporarily
comment E014 Read received data byte from ACIA
comment E017 Decode frame type (bits 3:2 determine status/data/cmd)
comment E01C Send acknowledgment byte back to GPIB controller
comment E021 Receive 3-byte command from GPIB controller
comment E026 Load command byte
comment E028 Check for 'q' (0x71) - query command
comment E02A Check for status commands: 'S'(0x53), 'T'(0x54), 'q'(0x71)
comment E02A These commands clear the GPIB link active flag
comment E037 Reset command state variables
comment E03A Clear command step counter
comment E03D Process command and build response
comment E040 Send 3-byte response back to GPIB controller
comment E043 Clear channel mode state bits
comment E049 Re-enable ACIA RX interrupts (write 0x91 to CSR)
comment E050 Return from interrupt

*=============================================================================
* Frame Type Decoder
*=============================================================================
comment E053 === DECODE UART FRAME TYPE FROM RX BITS 3:2 ===
comment E053 Bits 3:2 == 00: normal data (frame_type = 0)
comment E05C Bits 3:2 == 10: status update (frame_type = 1)
comment E066 Bits 3:2 == 11: status + data (frame_type = 3)
comment E070 Bits 3:2 == 01: data only (frame_type = 2)

*=============================================================================
* ACIA Byte-Level I/O
*=============================================================================
comment E079 === RECV 3 BYTES FROM ACIA ===
comment E079 Receive bytes into acia_rx_cmd, acia_rx_data_hi, acia_rx_data_lo
comment E079 Returns Z=1 on success, Z=0 on timeout/error

comment E099 === SEND BYTE VIA ACIA ===
comment E099 Wait for TX buffer empty, send byte from ACCB
comment E09C Poll ACIA status for TDRE (bit 1)
comment E0AB Write byte to ACIA data register
comment E0AF Return Z=1 on success

comment E0B1 === RECV BYTE FROM ACIA ===
comment E0B1 Wait for RX buffer full, receive byte into ACCB
comment E0BF Return Z=0 on timeout
comment E0C4 Return Z=0 on ACIA error
comment E0C9 Return Z=1 on success

comment E0CE === SEND 3 BYTES VIA ACIA ===
comment E0CE Send acia_tx_cmd, acia_tx_data_hi, acia_tx_data_lo

*=============================================================================
* GPIB Command Processing
*=============================================================================
comment E0EE === PROCESS GPIB COMMAND ===
comment E0EE Copy RX buffer to TX buffer (echo command)
comment E100 Test frame_type: if even, check for special commands
comment E107 Check for 'S' (0x53): serial poll → enable remote
comment E10E Check for 'U' (0x55): status update
comment E112 Check for 'V' (0x56): device clear

comment E11F === COMMAND DISPATCH VIA JUMP TABLE ===
comment E122 Subtract 'A' (0x41) from command byte to get table index
comment E125 Double index for 16-bit pointers (ASLB)
comment E126 Check bounds: index must be <= 0x31 (commands 'A'-'r')
comment E12B Load jump address from table at E14F + index
comment E143 Jump to command handler

